All Classes

  • Class Description
    Bank
    This class denotes the bank object of the game which gives and collects money from players.
    Board
    The Board class contains the methods and properties for initiailzing and progressing the game.
    Card
    This class denotes the Card object of the game, this also contains all the commands of the card chosen.
    Category1
    This object class extends the Card object to provide the implementations needed for cards which can be stored that allow a player to get out of jail.
    Category2
    This object, Category2, represents the cards that contains the capabilities that proceed to a nearest space such as, properties, utilities, or railroads.
    Category2A
    Category2A represents as the subclass of Category2 that focuses on the Property Space type in moving the player to the nearest Property
    Category2B
    Category2B represents as the subclass of Category2 that focuses on the Property Space type in moving the player to the nearest Utility This contains a property, diceRoll, used to store values from 1 - 6 obtained in implementing goToSpace
    Category2C
    This class extends Category2 which allows the player to go to nearest Railroad.
    Category3
    This category extends Cards class which is a category which has the implementation of giving money to the player.
    Category3A
    This class extends the Category3 class to denote that the card can only implement collectMoney
    Category3B
    This object represents a sub-class of Category 2 which adds the capabilities of changing the location of a player
    Category4
    This class extends Card class in order to identify the Cards under Category4 which implements GoTo and CollectMoney
    Category4A
    This class extends Category4 to and implements GoTo which changes the location of the player
    Category4B
    This class extends Card4 class to denote cards which are under category 4 which implement the GoTo and CollectMoney interfaces This would apply the effect of going to the nearest property
    Category5
    This class extends Card category to denote cards which belong under Category5 This primarily focuses on buffing a property, utility or railroad space owned by the player.
    Category5A
    Category 5A extends Category 5 which contains the implementations of double rent to a property
    Category5B
    This class extends Category5 class to denote that the card will renovate the property space of the player.
    Category5C
    This class extends Category5 to denote cards that update the chance percent of a space (Property, Utility or Railroqd)
    Category5CA
    This object extends Category extends Category5C which focuses on updating the rent percentage of a Property object
    Category5CB
    This object extends Category extends Category5C which focuses on updating the rent percentage of a Utility or Railroad object
    Category6
    This class extends the Card class to denote cards that collect random amounts of money from the player.
    CollectMoney
    Interface for Collecting Money from Player
    Deck
    This class denotes the deck object of the game which initializes, shuffles and contains all of the chance cards in the game.
    Dice
    The Dice class provides methods for the game to roll a dice by generating random values
    EmpireController  
    EmpireGUI  
    GoTo
    This interface includes the need for implementing the method for changing the location of a player
    JailOut
    Interface for Getting Player out of Jail
    Main  
    Money
    The Money class is responsible for the behaviors of the game involving the amount of cash and the transactions that occur.
    Ownable
    Interface that denotes if the card can be owned or not
    PayMoneyBank
    Interface which allows player to pay money to bank.
    Player
    This object class represents the players that will be moving in the game.
    Property
    This extends the Space class to implement several methods and properties that indicate the behaviors of a Property.
    Railroad
    This class implements several methods and properties that display the behaviors of a Railroad by extending the Space class
    Space
    This class Space contains methods and properties needed to identify each field or block in the game.
    Spacee
    This class is an extension of Space class to denote the following Space Types: Chance Luxury Tax Income Tax Start Jail Community Service Parking
    Upgrade
    Buffs a space Property, Utility or Railroad
    Utility
    This class extends the Space class for implementing methods and properties to indicate the behaviors of a Utility.
